The paper deals with a graph problem that involves selecting a set of vertices with certain distance constraints, which is a classic topic in graph theory and algorithms. The use of structural parameters such as treewidth and tree-depth suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The study of the problem's complexity with respect to graph parameters such as vertex cover and feedback vertex set suggests that it may also belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the mention of an FPT approximation scheme suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
